mdi web page the michelson doppler imager welcome to the home page of the soho michelson doppler imager mdi project the mdi observation program was terminated on 12 april 2011 mdi has been superseded by its offspring sdo hmi mdi data will continue to be available via these pages for a while it will be accessible via the sdo jsoc data center so long as the sdo mission continues mdi is a project of the stanford lockheed institute for space research and is a joint effort of the solar oscillations investigation soi in the ww hansen experimental physics laboratory of stanford university and the solar and astrophysics laboratory of the lockheed martin advanced technology center soi and the mdi team are part of an international collaboration to study the interior structure and dynamics of the sun the mdi team was responsible for the design and fabrication and now for the operation of the mdi instrument on board the solar and heliospheric observatory soho spacecraft general info science objectives & proposals results images & documentation data services & info operations other links press releases solar center stanford solar group
